10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em>=C2=A0If=
 you are Elon Musk, please stop reading this newsletter right now. You have=
 like six companies to run! Get back to work. For the rest of you: Money St=
uff will be off tomorrow and Monday, back on Tuesday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Oh Elon: Where we are</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Let=E2=80=99s just do a roundup of Elon-Musk-b=
uying-Twitter-Inc.-again news. First, technically, <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDUvbXVzay10d2l0dGVyLWp1ZGdlLXNheXMtb=
2N0LTE3LXRyaWFsLWlzLXN0aWxsLW9uLWZvci1ub3c_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAwNjIyX01PTkVZU1RV=
RkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMDA=
2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB970bb81c" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">  the trial=E2=80=99s still on</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The trial in Twitter Inc.=E2=80=99s lawsuit ag=
ainst Elon Musk remains on track to begin on Oct. 17 because the court has =
not yet received an agreement from the parties to put the case on hold, the=
 Delaware judge overseeing the matter said in a letter Wednesday. =E2=80=A6=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe parties have not filed a stipulat=
ion to stay this action, nor has any party moved for a stay,=E2=80=9D Judge=
 Kathaleen St. J. McCormick said in the Wednesday letter. =E2=80=9CI, there=
fore, continue to press on toward our trial set to begin on October 17, 202=
2.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk has said that he now wants to close the m=
erger on the original terms, and Twitter obviously wants that too. There ar=
e some much-too-cute ways that this can end=C2=A0<em>without=C2=A0</em>that=
 happening (mainly: He could be kidding, or his financing could fall throug=
h), and this whole thing has been much too cute and surprised me pretty con=
stantly, so I wouldn=E2=80=99t rule anything out. But probably they will cl=
ose the merger pretty soon.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are no real impediments to closing: The =
deal has gotten the necessary shareholder and regulatory approvals, and Mus=
k=E2=80=99s banks haven=E2=80=99t <em>said=C2=A0</em>anything publicly abou=
t the financing falling through.=C2=A0Still, you have to=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0<=
/em>the closing. That=E2=80=99s not nothing. The deal lawyers for Musk and =
Twitter =E2=80=94=C2=A0not the litigators who have been fighting each other=
 for months, but the people who wrote the merger agreement back in April wh=
en they were friends, and who probably haven=E2=80=99t spoken to each other=
 in a while =E2=80=94=C2=A0have to work together on a checklist of document=
s to sign, filings to make=C2=A0and wire transfers to send. Musk has to wir=
e $33.5 billion of his own money, which presumably is not all in his checki=
ng account right now, so he might need some time to put it in the right acc=
ounts. Musk=E2=80=99s bankers have to put up $13 billion of their money, an=
d they will have some processes to do that. This could all be done in a few=
 days, but it is work, and everyone has to work together to do it. They mig=
ht be a bit out of practice.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What Musk apparently wants is to pause the tri=
al while they can work this all out: <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9l=
ZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMTA1Nzg3L3RtMjIyNzQzNWQxX2V4OTktcy5=
odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBaa3c17ba" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> He offered to</a> =E2=80=
=9Cproceed to closing of the transaction,=E2=80=9D but only =E2=80=9Cprovid=
ed that the Delaware Chancery Court enter an immediate stay of the action .=
..=C2=A0and adjourn the trial.=E2=80=9D What Twitter wants is sort of the o=
pposite, to keep the pressure of a trial on Musk until he shows up with the=
 money. This feels like a solvable problem =E2=80=94=C2=A0basically, you wr=
ite some sort of agreement that says like =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re going to w=
ork together to get the closing done this week, but if we don=E2=80=99t we=
=E2=80=99re gonna have an extra-super-bad trial,=E2=80=9D and you get Chanc=
ellor McCormick to bless it =E2=80=94 but they=C2=A0have to work together t=
o solve it. They have to negotiate and draft an Agreement to Stick to the=
=C2=A0Agreement. If you=E2=80=99re writing that agreement, you have some tr=
ust issues.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Wall Street Journal <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNv=
bS9hcnRpY2xlcy9lbG9uLW11c2stYW5kLXR3aXR0ZXItZGlzY3Vzc2VkLXByaWNlLWN1dC10by0=
0NC1iaWxsaW9uLXRha2VvdmVyLWluLXJlY2VudC13ZWVrcy0xMTY2NTAxNzc4OD9tb2Q9aHBfbG=
VhZF9wb3Mx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1ad15103" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As of late Wednesday, representati=
ves of Mr. Musk and Twitter were trying to hash out the details of his prop=
osal this week to stick to that original agreement, the people familiar wit=
h the matter said. Sticking points include what would be required from both=
 sides for litigation over the stalled deal to be dropped and whether the d=
eal=E2=80=99s closing would be contingent on Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s receiving t=
he necessary debt financing, some of the people said.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Under the terms of the original agreement, the=
 closing=C2=A0<em>was=C2=A0</em>more or less contingent on the debt financi=
ng: If Musk=E2=80=99s banks did not come up with the $13 billion they have =
promised, Musk did not have to close, though he would have to pay a $1 bill=
ion termination fee. Under the current circumstances, I don=E2=80=99t think=
 that either Twitter or a judge would be very satisfied with that result. I=
 don=E2=80=99t think the lawsuit is going to be dropped until Twitter is su=
re that the banks will fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One notable deadline for resolving this was=C2=
=A0<em>today</em>, when Musk was supposed to have his deposition in the law=
suit, but I guess <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjI=
tMTAtMDYvbXVzay1wbGFucy10by1za2lwLWRlcG9zaXRpb24taW4tdHdpdHRlci1idXlvdXQtbG=
F3c3VpdD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDA2MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb=
3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc55537f6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  that=E2=80=99s on hold now</a>=
:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk won=E2=80=99t be showing=
 up Thursday for a long-awaited deposition in Twitter Inc.=E2=80=99s lawsui=
t aimed at forcing him to go through with a $44 billion buyout of the compa=
ny, according to people familiar with the matter. ... The deposition was sc=
heduled to start at 9:30 a.m. at a law firm=E2=80=99s offices in Austin, Te=
xas.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The simplest reading of the situation=C2=A0is =
that he paid $44 billion to get out of having to do that deposition.</p>
