<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The New York Times <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb=
20vMjAyMi8xMC8wNS90ZWNobm9sb2d5L2Vsb24tbXVzay10d2l0dGVyLWRpc2NvdW50Lmh0bWw/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4563c929" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reported last night</a> that Mu=
sk had been=C2=A0trying<em>=C2=A0</em>to get the price down, but had no luc=
k:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the weeks before Elon Musk declared that hi=
s bid to own Twitter was back on the table, his representatives spoke with =
the company several times about redoing the deal at a lower price, four peo=
ple familiar with the discussions said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Musk sought a discount of as much as 30 pe=
rcent, three of the people said, a proposal that would have valued the comp=
any at roughly $31 billion. Twitter rebuffed the proposal, said the people,=
 who requested anonymity because the talks were confidential.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the past week, however, discussions narrowe=
d to a discount of about 10 percent, which would have allowed Mr. Musk to p=
ay about $39.6 billion for Twitter. Those talks ultimately did not move for=
ward. Twitter=E2=80=99s market cap as of Wednesday was $39.2 billion.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around here I love writing imaginary dialogue =
for Elon Musk, but this one is kind of boring:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> Okay I tell you what, l=
et=E2=80=99s put all this behind us. I=E2=80=99ll drop my termination and b=
uy you for $38.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong> $54.20.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> $42?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong>=C2=A0 $54.20.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> $49? Come on that=E2=80=
=99s just 10% off our original deal price, the market has cracked, you stil=
l have a ton of risk that I will=E2=80=94</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong> $54.20.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong> $54.20.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> $54.20, final offer.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong> Fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> So we=E2=80=99re done?<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong> We=E2=80=99re done w=
hen your check clears.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Good for them! I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDUvZWxvbi1zLWJhY2s_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAwNj=
IyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX=
3Rlcm09MjIxMDA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa8=
14e90c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">  said yesterday</a> that, given the strength of its legal =
position, Twitter could not really justify knocking more than a couple of b=
ucks off the deal price. And given that=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>would requi=
re new shareholder approvals, delay closing=C2=A0and introduce new risks (w=
hat if he backed out of=C2=A0<em>that </em>deal?), it=E2=80=99s hardly wort=
h it. Just stick to $54.20. Musk seems to have come around.</p>
