<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In so much of business, there are different wa=
ys=C2=A0to describe the same conduct, and the different descriptions have d=
ifferent legal implications. =E2=80=9CI paid a bribe to a politician to get=
 this government contract=E2=80=9D: no, bad, don=E2=80=99t say that. =E2=80=
=9CWe do not have extensive contacts in that region, so I paid a consulting=
 fee to a firm with deep local knowledge, and they were able to advise us o=
n how to tailor our proposal effectively to the right decisionmakers=E2=80=
=9D: Isn=E2=80=99t that so calm and boring and business-y? Don=E2=80=99t yo=
ur eyes glaze over as you think =E2=80=9Csure, yes, business, whatever=E2=
=80=9D? Does it mean the same thing? Quite possibly!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or:=C2=A0=E2=80=9CHe blackmailed me, so I hand=
ed him a sack of cash=E2=80=9D: bad. =E2=80=9CHe gave me a copy of his alle=
gations as part of a confidential offer of settlement, and, without admitti=
ng or denying them, I decided to put the matter behind me by entering into =
a monetary settlement, which of course included a non-disclosure agreement=
=E2=80=9D: Isn=E2=80=99t that so calm and boring and lawyer-y? Don=E2=80=99=
t you think =E2=80=9Csure, yes, settlement, whatever=E2=80=9D? Does it mean=
 the same thing? <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
9286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
