90ZXJtPTIyMTAwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7=
3784a6b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  Quite possibly</a>!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is extremely extremely extremely not lega=
l advice, do not try it at home, and often we find ourselves talking about =
these issues around here because someone thought they used the right words =
and prosecutors disagreed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s another important one. =E2=80=
=9CThey hacked into our system and stole our user data, so we paid them ran=
som to give it back=E2=80=9D: bad! Bad for them (they did a crime), and als=
o bad for you: You have to disclose =E2=80=94=C2=A0to the users, perhaps to=
 the government, perhaps to shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0that you got hacked=
, and you might get in trouble for your carelessness. =E2=80=9CWe have a bu=
g bounty program in which we pay rewards to outside security researchers wh=
o spot holes in our security, and that program worked as designed to catch =
this problem before it could be used by evil hackers=E2=80=9D: much nicer. =
Your bug bounty program working effectively is not a security=C2=A0<em>fail=
ing</em>, it is a security=C2=A0<em>success</em>, and you don=E2=80=99t hav=
e to report it to anyone.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Boy is that not legal advice, that=E2=80=99s l=
ike the opposite of legal advice, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/29286274.284524/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDUvdWJlci1zLWZvcm1lci1zZWN1cml0eS1jaGllZi1pcy1jb252aW=
